results.name: Decimal expansion of the power tower of Euler constant gamma.
link: Stanislav Sykora, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..2000
formula: In general, for 1/E^E <= c < 1, c^c^c^... = LambertW(log(1/c))/log(1/c). Hence, this number is LambertW(log(1/gamma))/log(1/gamma).
mathematica: c = EulerGamma; RealDigits[ ProductLog[-Log[c]]/Log[c], 10, 111] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Oct 24 2014 *)
